<br />
<br />One other problem that I noticed (I couldn't notice any others) that's really minor: That jumpsprings in worlds that allow very high jumping are green, not red.  In this NES port, they are red in all cases.  I'm still trying to figure out exactly how the FDS version turns them green in the first place, and why it doesn't work in the NES port.  (It's probably the same as the pirhana plant problem, and issue with writing to PRG-RAM, which doesn't exist on the NES except for the pseudo PRG-RAM at $6000-$7fff set up by this port.

		

